  "lemmas": {
    "OPEN": {
      "name": "OPEN_kappa_constructive_and_deployed_Mpad",
      "statement": "(1) Constructive \u03ba: residual free-1 highs \u2192 [2176] from fiber/ledger geometry (naive tags banked negative in toys).\n(2) M_pad\u22641 or \u22642 at free_core=846161: intersection packing only gives a huge binomial ratio; need residual/split constraints beyond |C\u2229C'|\u2264free_core\u22121.",
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    "fc1_recovery": {
      "name": "free_core_1_disjoint_packing_recovered",
      "proof": [
        "Intersection theorem + v25/v26 packing."
      ],
      "statement": "free_core=1 \u21d2 |C\u2229C'|\u22640 \u21d2 multipad cores pairwise disjoint \u2286 D\\(U\u222aV) with |U\u222aV|=2e \u21d2 M_pad \u2264 \u230a(n\u22122e)/m_c\u230b.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "intersection": {
      "deployed_free_core": 846161,
      "deployed_intersection_bound": 846160,
      "name": "multipad_core_intersection_le_free_core_minus_1",
      "proof": [
        "v22: multipad cores are depth-w multi-mates: Phi_w(C)=Phi_w(C'), so \u0394 := \u039b_C \u2212 \u039b_{C'} has deg(\u0394) \u2264 m_c \u2212 w \u2212 1 = free_core \u2212 1.",
        "C \u2260 C' monic same degree \u21d2 \u0394 \u2260 0.",
        "If r \u2208 C \u2229 C' then \u039b_C(r)=\u039b_{C'}(r)=0 \u21d2 \u0394(r)=0.",
        "A nonzero univariate polynomial of degree \u2264 d over a field has at most d roots. Hence |C \u2229 C'| \u2264 deg(\u0394) \u2264 free_core \u2212 1."
      ],
      "statement": "If C \u2260 C' are multipad cores (share free-1 CS sides (U,V) in one j-fiber), then |C \u2229 C'| \u2264 free_core \u2212 1, where free_core = m_c \u2212 w = j \u2212 2w \u2212 1.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "kappa_criterion": {
      "deployed_K_max": 2176,
      "name": "high_tag_criterion_restated",
      "proof": [
        "v26 high-tag payment criterion."
      ],
      "statement": "M_pad\u22641 and residual highs \u21aa [K] with K\u00b7\u230an/e\u230b\u2264e (deployed K\u22642176) \u21d2 (\u03ba,\u03b9,\u03b4) injects residual free-1 CS pairs into e\u00b7p \u21d2 |A_SP|\u2264t\u00b7p.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "uniform_packing": {
      "deployed": {
        "free_core": 846161,
        "log10_bound_estimate": 478050.28,
        "m_c": 913632,
        "n_minus_2e": 1962208,
        "note": "Ratio is ~10^478050 (log10 via lgamma) \u2014 useless for M_pad\u22642."
      },
      "name": "multipad_uniform_intersection_packing",
      "proof": [
        "If two m_c-sets both contain the same (s+1)-set T, then their intersection has size \u2265 s+1 > s, contradicting the intersection bound.",
        "Hence the map core \u21a6 its family of (s+1)-subsets is disjointly supported.",
        "Count: M_pad \u00b7 C(m_c, s+1) \u2264 C(n\u22122e, s+1)."
      ],
      "statement": "Let s = free_core \u2212 1. Among multipad cores for fixed (U,V), every pair intersects in \u2264 s points, so each core's (s+1)-subsets are exclusive. With ground set D\\(U\u222aV) of size n\u22122e and |core|=m_c: M_pad \u2264 C(n\u22122e, s+1) / C(m_c, s+1) = C(n\u22122e, free_core) / C(m_c, free_core).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    }
  },
